Package io.xmljim.algorithms.model

Interface Parameterized

All Superinterfaces:
NamedEntity, VariableEntity
All Known Subinterfaces:
Function<T>, Model, ScalarFunction
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractParameterized
public interface Parameterized
extends VariableEntity
A base interface for any entity requiring parameters (e.g., functions, models). Parameters should be accessible by name (NamedEntity.getName()), variable (VariableEntity.getVariable()) (if present), and parameter type (Parameter.getParameterType()).

Parameters and parameter values can be access using the find(Predicate) method that uses predicates to locate the requested parameter, or using any of the get* methods, some of which use the find method.

  • Method Details

    • getParameter

      default Optional<Parameter<?>> getParameter​(String name)
      Return an optional (nullable) of a parameter by name. Using an Optional allows for consumers to implement specific logic in the event that the named parameter is not present.
      Parameters:
      name - the parameter name
      Returns:
      an optional parameter. Note that if more than one parameter exists for a given name, then the first parameter found is returned

    • getParameter

      default Optional<Parameter<?>> getParameter​(String name, String variable)
      Return an optional parameter by both name and variable. Using an Optional allows for consumers to implement specific logic in the event that the named parameter is not present.
      Parameters:
      name - the parameter name
      variable - the variable
      Returns:
      an optional parameter that can be accessed through Optional.get()

    • parameterNameVariable

      default Predicate<Parameter<?>> parameterNameVariable​(String name, String variable)
      Predicate for locating a parameter by name and variable

      Syntactic sugar for the applying the lambda 

      p -> p.getName().equals(name) && p.getVariable().equals(variable)}

      Internally uses predicate chaining using the Predicate.and(Predicate) method to combine parameterName(String) and parameterVariable(String) predicates into a single predicate

      Parameters:
      name - the parameter name
      variable - the parameter variable
      Returns:
      the predicate for locating a parameter by name and variable

    • parameterType

      Parameters:
      parameterType - the parameter name
      Returns:
      the predicate for locating a parameter by name and variable
